{
  "uuid": "d5def68025b7b6607e3a8985bcc94e0c",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations Manager (Transport)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Main Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Operations & Fleet Management</p><ul><li><p>Assist the Director in overseeing daily operations.</p></li><li><p>Ensure timely and efficient delivery of goods while optimising fleet utilisation.</p></li><li><p>Monitor vehicle maintenance, servicing schedules, fuel consumption, and repair works.</p></li><li><p>Handle operational issues such as delays, breakdowns, and last-minute changes effectively.</p></li></ul><p>People Management</p><ul><li><p>Supervise, lead, and support drivers, dispatchers, and operations staff.</p></li><li><p>Conduct performance reviews, training, and coaching to improve productivity and service quality.</p></li><li><p>Manage staffs attendance, discipline, and adherence to company policies and SOPs.</p></li></ul><p>Compliance & Safety</p><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with Singapore regulations (LTA, MOM, WSH requirements).</p></li><li><p>Implement and enforce safety standards, operational procedures, and company policies.</p></li><li><p>Investigate incidents or accidents and implement corrective actions.</p></li></ul><p>Customer & Stakeholder Management</p><ul><li><p>Liaise with customers, warehouses, suppliers, and internal departments to ensure smooth operations.</p></li><li><p>Handle customer feedback, complaints, and service recovery professionally.</p></li></ul><p>Reporting & Continuous Improvement</p><ul><li><p>Monitor KPIs such as on-time delivery, fleet utilization, operating costs, and safety performance.</p></li><li><p>Prepare operational reports and provide recommendations for improvement.</p></li><li><p>Assist Direct in budgeting, cost control, and operational planning.<br /></p><p>Preferably with Class 3/4 license will be added advantage</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
